## Completeness Checklist
- [ ] Project overview is clear and readable by non-technical stakeholders
- [ ] All objectives have measurable success criteria
- [ ] In scope and out of scope explicitly defined
- [ ] AI justification explains why AI is necessary (not just what AI does)
- [ ] Fallback scenario documented — product viable without AI
- [ ] Governance structure defined with named individuals where possible
- [ ] Budget estimates cover all categories with confidence levels
- [ ] Key milestones aligned to gate model
- [ ] Constraints documented; assumptions listed with risk if invalidated
- [ ] Risks summary references the Initial Risk Register
- [ ] All required signatories identified

## Handover Readiness
<!-- Confirms this artefact is ready for formal handover to Gate A review. -->
- [ ] Project Charter signed off by all required stakeholders
- [ ] All referenced artefacts (Problem Statement, Vision Statement, Stakeholder Map, Feasibility Assessment, Initial Risk Register) are complete and linked
- [ ] No open critical risks without mitigation plans
- [ ] Budget approved or formally under review
- [ ] Document version controlled and stored in the project artefact repository
- [ ] Ready for inclusion in Gate A Pack
